title: Frieze, 1905–15
inscribed: Printed in selvedge: "York Card & Paper Co; pattern number "1672".
description: Mission style. Alternating large and small stylized red tulips. The large tulips are enveloped in cream laurels. The small tulips are enframed in a polka-dotted structure outlined in a dark brown glossy pigment. Bottom has scrolling vine and band of glossy brown pigment. Top is a band of green with beading and a brown glossy band with widely spaced three-leaf clusters. Lower half of background ornamented with dots and vertical stripes. Ground shades dark to light beige, bottom to top. Printed in selvedge: "York Card & Paper Co"; pattern number "1672".

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1905–15.
1905–15. Machine-printed on paper. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-342.
